## 4. Styling Rules

### CSS Token System

All custom styling in `packages/client/src/styles/app.css` using PF tokens:

```css
.app-status-card {
  padding: var(--pf-t--global--spacer--md);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--pf-t--global--color--status--success--default);
  background: var(--pf-t--global--background--color--secondary--default);
  border-radius: var(--pf-t--global--border--radius--small);
}
```

### Rules

- NO hardcoded `px` for spacing -- use `--pf-t--global--spacer--*`
- NO hex/rgb colors -- use `--pf-t--global--color--*` tokens
- NO inline `style` props in JSX
- Prefix custom classes with `app-` to avoid PF collisions
- NO targeting PF internal class names in selectors
- NO `!important` overrides of PF styles

### Dark Mode

- All custom CSS automatically works in dark mode when using PF tokens
- Toggle dark mode: `document.documentElement.classList.toggle('pf-v6-theme-dark')`
- Test both themes during development

